<h1 class="text-xl font-bold mb-8">Bio</h1>

<div class="prose lg:prose-md">
    <p>Mason Wheeler is a recent graduate in Electrical and Computer Engineering from the University of Washington, with a unique background that blends athletics and technology. As a former UW Football athlete, Mason learned the value of discipline, teamwork, and perseverance - lessons that continue to shape his approach to both personal and professional growth.</p>

    <p>With a deep fascination for technology, particularly in areas where high performance computing, machine learning, and quantum computing intersect, Mason specialized in the Machine Learning Pathway during his studies. This focus honed his skills in designing and implementing intelligent systems.</p>

    <p>Beyond his technical abilities, Mason is known for his capacity to listen and learn from others, especially those whose communication style might be considered challenging. This trait has made him highly coachable and has allowed him to connect ideas from diverse disciplines, fostering a multifaceted perspective on problem-solving.</p>

    <p>Mason strongly believes in the power of small, consistent actions in shaping character. Whether it's in the way he treats strangers, respects others' time, or handles everyday tasks, he strives to embody the values of reliability, respect, and continuous improvement in all aspects of his life.</p>

    <p>Now embarking on his professional journey as a Software Engineer at Microsoft, Mason is excited to contribute to innovative systems while continuing to grow both as an engineer and as a person. He is particularly passionate about using his experiences to advocate for diversity in sports and tech, hoping to inspire others to push beyond perceived limitations.</p>

    <p>At his core, Mason is someone who believes in the connection between discipline, continuous learning, and success - always aiming to be better today than he was yesterday.</p>
